sec.p:
Age, sex, ethnicity, and socioeconomic status were considered as potential predictor variables for the probability of mature clavicles. The method of clavicle examination was further considered as a factor influencing the probability of being diagnosed with mature clavicles. Age and socioeconomic status (i.e., HDI) were analyzed as covariates. Sex, ethnicity, and the method of clavicle examination were analyzed as fixed factors. Possible interaction between these fixed factors and the covariate age was also investigated. The initial (exploratory) logit model may be described by the following equation:
